DSA Interview Notes – LeetCode 238: Product of Array Except Self
Problem Statement

Given an integer array nums, return an array answer such that:

answer[i] = Product of all elements of nums except nums[i]
Constraints
Do not use the division operator.
Solve the problem in O(n) time complexity.
Example
Input
nums = [1,2,3,4]
Output
[24,12,8,6]
Explanation
Index 0
2 × 3 × 4 = 24

Index 1
1 × 3 × 4 = 12

Index 2
1 × 2 × 4 = 8

Index 3
1 × 2 × 3 = 6
Step 1 – Understanding the Problem

For every element, we need to calculate:

Product of all elements except itself.
Step 2 – Brute Force Approach
Idea

For every index i, traverse the complete array again and multiply every element except the current one.

Algorithm
for each index i

    product = 1

    for each index j

        if(i != j)

            product *= nums[j]

    answer[i] = product
Time Complexity
O(n²)

Reason:

For every element, we traverse the entire array again.

Step 3 – Observation

Consider:

nums = [1,2,3,4]

For index 2

1  2 |3| 4

Required Answer

1 × 2 × 4

This can be written as:

(Product of Left Side)

×

(Product of Right Side)

This observation is the key to the optimal solution.

Main Idea

Instead of calculating

Product of all elements except itself

Think of it as

Product of Left Side

×

Product of Right Side
