Optimal Approach

The solution requires two traversals.

First Traversal (Left → Right)

Goal:

Store the product of all elements present on the left side of every index.

Initialize

leftProduct = 1;

Algorithm

Store leftProduct into answer[i]

Update

leftProduct = leftProduct × nums[i]
Dry Run
nums = [1,2,3,4]
Index	leftProduct	Answer
0	1	1
1	1	1
2	2	2
3	6	6

After first traversal

answer = [1,1,2,6]

Meaning

answer[i]

=

Product of all elements before index i
Second Traversal (Right → Left)

Goal:

Multiply the product of all right-side elements into the answer array.

Initialize

rightProduct = 1;

Algorithm

answer[i] = answer[i] × rightProduct

Update

rightProduct = rightProduct × nums[i]
Dry Run
Index	rightProduct	answer[i]
3	1	6
2	4	8
1	12	12
0	24	24

Final Answer

[24,12,8,6]